.TH "ntfs_get_nr_significant_bytes" 9 "ntfs_get_nr_significant_bytes" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ntfs_get_nr_significant_bytes \- get number of bytes needed to store a number
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ntfs_get_nr_significant_bytes
.BI "(const s64 n "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "n" 12
number for which to get the number of bytes for
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return the number of bytes required to store \fIn\fP unambiguously as
a signed number.

This is used in the context of the mapping pairs array to determine how
many bytes will be needed in the array to store a given logical cluster
number (lcn) or a specific run length.

Return the number of bytes written.  This function cannot fail.
